function! s:f1() abort
  let x = [1, 2, 3]
  call s:f2(x)
  echo x
endfunction

function! s:f2(x) abort
  let a:x[1] = 'gorilla'
endfunction

call s:f1() "=> [1, 'gorilla', 3]

vimhelp 20Êó• 12:29:41 Slack 

                                                        *word*
A word consists of a sequence of letters, digits and underscores, or a
sequence of other non-blank characters, separated with white space (spaces,
tabs, <EOL>).  This can be changed with the 'iskeyword' option.  An empty line
is also considered to be a word.

Suppress creation of backup files ¬∑ Issue #14 ¬∑ lambdalisue/suda.vim
When opening files that only root can read using suda, nvim will still create a world-readable backup file. For files containing sensitive information, this is highly undesirable.
